<br>
My main reasons to gripe are the following.<br>
<br>
1)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp We were naturally giving much lower spec points, and hit points, lowering our ability for damage output and or most of our defense. <br>
2)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 12 points is a very considerable amount.  It can be used to get more defensive skills such as mastery of parry and block for pure tanks.  Also it can be used for mastery of pain helping out damage.  These things are already a disadvantage to a Skald. <br>
3)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Defense has been giving to many classes that in all honesty should not be built for it.  Friars and Stealthier have powerful high level evade, we all know what that is like.  RA’s can make up partially for this problem.  Other tanks in the game also with the greater spec points have easily much more defense.  I don’t dispute that this should be how it is but introducing RA’s that have a cost difference has further widened the gap of defense.<br>
4)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp We do not have access to any type of powerful realm abilities.  We lack the ability to spend points on determination.  As someone who once had Fury of the Gods I can say it will likely compete to be one of the worst RA’s in the game.  <br>
<br>
My point being that we are getting hit with a double whammy here.  Fewer hits, specs and damage, at the same time more expensive RA’s.  This is very frustrating logic.  Evade 1 and 5 parry is all my defense amounts to.  I had to sacrifice a lot of parry to get a non 50 but decent weapon spec.  No class in the game has such poor defense.  Our close relatives the Minstrels have evade 2.  All fighters in all the realms have 2.0 spec except for the Skald.  Making it more expensive for us to spend our realm points is ridiculous! <br>
<br>
<br>
